briefdescription.para: This function locks a locking object.

detaileddescription.para: All other threads that call this function before this thread calls the _SlNonOsLockObjUnlock would be suspended

parameterdescription.para: - pointer to the locking object control block

- numeric value specifies the maximum number of mSec to stay suspended while waiting for the locking object Currently, the simple link driver uses only two values:
NONOS_WAIT_FOREVER
NONOS_NO_WAIT

simplesect.para: upon successful reception of the locking object the function should return 0 Otherwise, a negative value indicating the error code shall be returned

briefdescription.para: This function unlock a locking object.

parameterdescription.para: - pointer to the locking object control block

simplesect.para: upon successful unlocking the function should return 0 Otherwise, a negative value indicating the error code shall be returned

briefdescription.para: This function waits for a sync signal of the specific sync object.

- numeric value specifies the maximum number of mSec to stay suspended while waiting for the sync signal Currently, the simple link driver uses only two values:

briefdescription.para: type definition for the return values of this adaptation layer
type definition for a sync object container

detaileddescription.para: Sync object is object used to synchronize between two threads or thread and interrupt handler. One thread is waiting on the object and the other thread send a signal, which then release the waiting thread. The signal must be able to be sent from interrupt context. This object is generally implemented by binary semaphore or events.

briefdescription.para: type definition for a time value
This function must be called from the main loop in non-os paltforms.

simplesect.para: 0 - No more activities 1 - Activity still in progress

briefdescription.para: This function call the pEntry callback from a different context.

parameterdescription.para: - pointer to the entry callback function
- pointer to any type of memory structure that would be passed to pEntry callback from the execution thread.
- execution flags - reserved for future usage

simplesect.para: upon successful registration of the spawn the function return 0 (the function is not blocked till the end of the execution of the function and could be returned before the execution is actually completed) Otherwise, a negative value indicating the error code shall be returned
